  "market_context": "RTY opened within a gap on the daily and expanded away from the weekly low, creating failure swings. When price failed to manipulate the internal high lower, the analyst shifted bias to trust the weekly low and target the external high as draw on liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "Price failing to manipulate the internal high and continuing through it validated trusting the weekly low and trading away from failure swings toward the opposing range high, confirmed by a 4-hour SMT fill versus YM.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily, observe price opening within a gap and expanding away from the weekly low, creating failure swings.",
    "Step 2: Note price failed to manipulate the internal high lower, signalling it would instead manipulate the internal high and target the external high as draw on liquidity, trusting the weekly low.",
    "Step 3: On the 4-hour, identify 1800 forming the low of day expanding off the open, with an SMT fill versus YM (the correlated market for RTY).",
    "Step 4: Drop to the 30-minute and locate the 4-hour gap, confirmed by a lower-time-frame swing formation, cracking correlation between candle 2 and candle 3, and a CSD.",
    "Step 5: Confirm 9:30 expansion away from the reversal, validating the trade into the higher time frame draw on liquidity.",
    "Step 6: On the 15-minute, observe RTY trading into a gap while YM does not — a continuation PSP/SMT, with the 10 AM open forming the low of the 10 AM 4-hour candle into the 15-minute fair value gap confirmed by SMT.",
    "Step 7: Mark equilibrium of the 15-minute candle's range and require price to respect the upper half; use the fractal model on lower time frame for entry.",
    "Step 8: Drop to the 1-minute, observe V-shape reversal signature with expansion into the low (SMT) and expansion away, then enter a continuation order block / fair value gap retracement targeting the higher-time-frame high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Analyst entered the fair value gap on the 1-minute retracement and held approximately a three-hour trade targeting the higher-time-frame high, wrapping up his week.",
  "lessons": "When price fails to manipulate an internal high/low in the expected direction and continues through it, bias shifts to trusting the weekly extreme and targeting the opposing external liquidity. Multi-timeframe SMT, CSD, and V-shape reversal confluences provide high-probability continuation entries.",
